---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — joy·object"
  description="I'm joy, a product designer and creative technologist living in Oslo with more than a decade years of experience."
  navActive="about"
>
  <div class="about">
    <!-- Left Column: Header & Nav -->
    <div class="about__left-col">
      <header>
        <a
          href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL}
          class="type-logo home__logo"
          style="text-decoration:none;color:var(--gray-900);"
        >
          joy<span class="home__logo-dot"></span>object
        </a>
      </header>

      <nav class="about__nav">
        <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL} class="btn-light">Work</a>
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}about/`} class="btn-light is-active">
          About
          <span
            style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;width:20px;height:20px;"
          >
            <span
              style="width:4px;height:4px;background:var(--gray-900);border-radius:50%;display:block;"
            ></span>
          </span>
        </a>
      </nav>
    </div>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="about__content">
      <!-- Left: Portrait -->
      <div class="about__portrait-wrap">
        <img
          src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')}/images/about/joy-portrait.jpg`}
          alt="Joy working at desk"
          class="about__portrait"
          width="400"
          height="500"
        />
      </div>

      <!-- Right: Text -->
      <div class="about__right">
        <!-- ASCII Art -->
        <div class="about__ascii type-ascii">
          {
            `      ___           ___           ___       ___       ___     
     /\\__\\         /\\  \\         /\\__\\     /\\__\\     /\\  \\    
    /:/  /        /::\\  \\       /:/  /    /:/  /    /::\\  \\   
   /:/__/        /:/\\:\\  \\     /:/  /    /:/  /    /:/\\:\\  \\  
  /::\\  \\ ___   /::\\~\\:\\  \\   /:/  /    /:/  /    /:/  \\:\\  \\ 
 /:/\\:\\  /\\__\\ /:/\\:\\ \\:\\__\\ /:/__/    /:/__/    /:/__/ \\:\\__\\
 \\/__\\:\\/:/  / \\:\\~\\:\\ \\/__/ \\:\\  \\    \\:\\  \\    \\:\\  \\ /:/  /
      \\::/  /   \\:\\ \\:\\__\\    \\:\\  \\    \\:\\  \\    \\:\\  /:/  / 
      /:/  /     \\:\\ \\/__/     \\:\\  \\    \\:\\  \\    \\:\\/:/  /  
     /:/  /       \\:\\__\\        \\:\\__\\    \\:\\__\\    \\::/  /   
     \\/__/         \\/__/         \\/__/     \\/__/     \\/__/    `
          }
        </div>

        <!-- Intro -->
        <p class="about__intro">
          I'm Joy, a product designer living in Oslo. Starting out as an architect, I tend to see the whole system before I see the screen. I've always worked at the edge of technology and craft — that's where I find the most interesting problems to solve.
          Over the past decade I've specialised in turning genuinely complex technology (generative AI, spatial computing, carbon accounting) into products that feel intuitive and human.
        </p>

        <!-- Body -->
        <div class="about__body">
          <p>
            Currently I'm a design lead at <a href="http://skalar.no/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Skalar</a> in Oslo, where I defined the UX strategy for an AI-powered tool helping SMEs manage and report their carbon emissions. I'm also co-founder and designer at <a href="http://megalearn.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Megalearn</a>, where we're building a browser-based multiplayer educational game powered by generative AI and 3D environments.
          </p>
          <p>
            Previously, I spent four years as a Senior Product Designer at <a href="http://kahoot.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kahoot!</a>, designing core features including reports, courses, and gameplay animations for a platform used by over a billion players. Before that I held senior roles at <a href="https://podio.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Podio</a> (acquired by <a href="https://www.citrix.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Citrix</a>), <a href="https://www.brandwatch.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Brandwatch</a>), and Leo Innovation Lab — covering everything from social media tools to a dermatology platform for patients and oncologists.
          </p>

          <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400; line-height: 25px; letter-spacing: 0.4px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gray-600); margin-top: 48px; margin-bottom: 16px;">
            Education
          </h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
            I’m a lifelong learner with a background that spans three continents and multiple disciplines:
          </p>
          <ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 0; margin-bottom: 24px;">
            <li style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 21px; line-height: 32px; margin-bottom: 16px;">
              <strong>Architecture:</strong> M.Arch. from KU Leuven (cum laude) and B.Arch. from Chulalongkorn University (1st honours).
            </li>
            <li style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 21px; line-height: 32px; margin-bottom: 16px;">
              <strong>Games:</strong> M.Sc. Media Technology and Games from IT University of Copenhagen.
            </li>
            <li style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 21px; line-height: 32px; margin-bottom: 16px;">
              <strong>Manga:</strong> Research fellowship at Kyoto Seika University, focused on Shonen manga.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Download CV -->
        <div class="about__cv-btn">
          <a
            href="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/yhlreq9gdn46pm3bekvt7/Joy-CV-April-2026.pdf?rlkey=3rotx4qeflz0lju4jf29zzsue&st=koj8bpiu&dl=0"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="btn-dark">Download my CV</a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
